      • checkModCount

        protected void checkModCount()
        Checks for concurrent modification by examining the underlying map's modCount. Throws an exception if concurrent modification is detected.

      • resetModCount

        protected void resetModCount()
        Resets the iterator to be in sync with the map's latest modCount. This is used if this iterator makes a call to modify the underlying map, so that subsequent operations don't mistake the change for a concurrent modification.
